2.Mountain View Middle School is all set for organizing their elaborate talent show event of the year, "Stars Onstage". It is a fun-filled event for the students to showcase and build their confidence.

Of the total audience who had come for the show, 1/3 were boys, 3/6 were girls and the rest of them were adults. If there were 'x' more girls than adults, how many people were there in total? Help the School authorities to find the total people who visited their show.

Input Format

First line of the input is an integer 'x', which corresponds to the count of girls more than adults. Enter x 50

Constraints

nil

Output Format

150 people were there in total

Sample Input 0

20
Sample Output 0

60 people were there in total

Program
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int x=sc.nextInt();
        int adult=x/2;
        int girl=x+adult;
        int boy=girl-adult;
        int total=adult+girl+boy;
        System.out.println(total+" people were there in total");
        
    }
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3.Find the output for given input by using + - * /

Input Format

A single line input represents four space separated integers

Constraints

1<=a,b,c,d<=10000

Output Format

Each output based on the given input numbers

Sample Input 0

45
6
89
12
Sample Output 0

152
58
128
288360

program
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;
import java.text.*;
import java.math.*;
import java.util.regex.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int a=sc.nextInt();
        int b=sc.nextInt();
        int c=sc.nextInt();
        int d=sc.nextInt();
        int sum = a + b + c + d;
        int difference = a+b+c/d;
        int product = a+b+c-d;
        long complexProduct =a * b * c * d;

        // Print the results
        System.out.println(sum);
        System.out.println(difference);
        System.out.println(product);
        System.out.println(complexProduct);
    }
}
